9/1/98
  Discuss Autonomous frame pattern with group.
  I picture decoding is basically working.  Picture looks OK.
  Still some unconfirmed pixel mismatchs!

9/2/98
  Attended with Ji SCTE's DPI Ad Hoc Group meeting.

9/3/98
  Fixed several bugs from my decoder.

9/4/98
  Fixed more bugs from my decoder.
  Got segmentation error at B-picture 10 for the echo3 sequence.
  Have no idea why I got this bug!  Switched to use echo2 sequence instead
  to continue debugging.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9/8/98
  Attended 401k meeting.
  Review seamless splicing patent draft from Greg.
  Spent half of the day to debug the segmentation error.  Found a way to
  hide the bug.  Couldn't find the cause yet!

9/9/98
  Finish debugging MPEG2 decoder.  The segmentation error seems to disappear
  after I remove the debugging codes.
  Start working on MPEG2 encoder.

9/10/98
  Finally the benefit enrollment form was faxed to TriNet.  Reception confirmed.

  Modify usage of dc_dct_pred and intra block reconstruction so that they
  are as described in the spec.  The result is still 100% matching with
  mpeg2decode result for about 60 frames being tested.

  My encoder can now generate I-picture only bitstream with perfect
  reconstruction matching with my decoder.

9/11/98
  Working primarily on the motion estimation package.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9/14/98
  Response to patent attroney on his questions on the 6 splicing scenarios.
  Written a small email to break down the complexity of the anchor frame
  generation problem.

  Start debugging the encoder for P-picture.
  Fixed mb_type debugging:  P_INTRA done.

9/15/98
  Continue working on P-picture encoding.
  Tough bug: after calling swapBuffer() function in the main program,
             it hangs at frm 1, MB 102 on athens!  It funs fine in Lakers.
  Fixed mb_type: P_DPCM done.

9/16/98
  Explained cross picture-type re-encoding disadvantage and
  clarified B-picture reference dependency to Ji and Greg in a email.

  Debugged motion search module.
  Put in P-picture mode decision.
  Still need to fix motion vector prediction.

9/17/98
  Can now generate decodeable P-picture bitstream.  Still has mismatch
  between encoder and decoder.
  Video quality is very bad.  May have problem in mode decision.

9/18/98
  P-picture bitstreams now have perfect match between encoder, decoder, and
  MSSG decoder on a 30 picture test.  Pictures have no severe coding artifacts.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To do:
  Need to prepare slides for Wen.

9/21/98
  Finish simplifying the source code.  The final code has perfect match.
  Finish the code of encoding B picture. 

9/22/98
  PTO

9/23/98
  Review patent draft received.  Discussed with Ji.  I need to provide
  description on time stamp correction.

  B picture encode starts to work now.  Perfect match for 1 sec test.
  Speed test:  mpeg2dec: 36 sec.  mssg dec: 31 sec.
  Extended mpeg2dec to support transport stream input also.  Seems working!

9/24/98
  Added display option to mpeg2dec.

  Written up a more detailed description for the time stamp correction section
  in the patent.
  Response to the patent draft.

9/25/98
  DPI discussion with Fang, Ji, Wayne and Francesco to figure the event
  from PPC to DSP.

  Written and tested a program which can extract from a transport stream
  a PID stream, a PES stream or an elementary stream.

  Fixed several bugs of mpeg2dec based on the HITS bitstream.
  Now the decoder should be able to decode both EchoStar and HITS bitstreams.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9/28/98
  Found out that my decoder did not decode Wayne's bitstream because it does
  not currently support field pictures.

  Start working on the splicer program.
  The first mode will be simply cut and paste, with no re-encoding.

9/29/98
  Added buffer option for OutPort.

9/30/98
  Created 4 viewgraphs for Wen's presentation.

  Finished TR adjustment.
  Exit point (with B pictures) works.

